All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
FYPCoordinator
This class represents a FYP Coordinator who is responsible for handling various tasks related to FYP project management such as changing project supervisor, allocating project to student, deregistering student from project, generating project details report, and viewing all projects.
FYPCoordinatorModule
The FYPCoordinatorModule class is a User Interface class that provides a command-line interface for FYP Coordinator's functionalities.
FYPDB
The FYPDB class represents the database of the FYP system.
FYPManagementSystem
Main function and landing page for users.
LoginModule
This represents the login landing page after selecting the login option in the home page User will be required to log in as part of the basic security features Users can access Student, Supervisor, or FYPCoordinator
Project
This class represents a project that can be assigned to a student.
ProjectController
The ProjectController class is responsible for managing the projects in the FYP system.
ProjectStatus
This enum class represents the various project statuses that a project can have.
Request
This class represents a Request object which is used to request changes to a Project's properties.
Request_ChangeSupervisor
Represents a request to change the supervisor of a project.
Request_ChangeTitle
Represents a request to change the title of a project.
Request_DeregisterFYP
Represents a request to deregister a student from a project.
Request_RegisterFYP
This class represents a request to register for a final year project (FYP).
RequestStatus
This is an enum class which represents the RequestStatus for Request objects
RequestType
This is an enum class which represents the RequestType for Request objects It contains the different types of requests that can be made by a user for a FYP project such as changing the title, deregistering, registering, or changing supervisor
Student
The Student class represents a student user of the FYP system.
StudentModule
This represents the Student Module which will be accessed when the user logs in using a Student Account Upon succesful login as Student, the user will be presented with options available to a Student
Supervisor
The Supervisor class represents a supervisor user in the FYP System.
SupervisorModule
This represents the Supervisor Module which will be accessed when the user logs in using a Supervisor Account Upon successful login as Supervisor, the user will be presented with options available to a Supervisor
SystemInitializer
This class provides static methods for initializing the system with data from external files.
User
Represents a User superclass.
